# Mobile Viewport Testing

When making changes to comic reader or mobile layouts, the browser simulator shows the **full viewport** (no URL bar). On physical devices, the browser chrome takes ~50–100px, causing content to shift or be cut off.

## Simulate Physical Device in DevTools

1. **Custom device**: DevTools → Dimensions → Edit → Add custom device
   - Use reduced height (e.g. iPhone 14 Pro: 393×700 instead of 393×844)
2. **Responsive mode**: Set height manually ~100px less than device height
3. See `components/comicReader/MOBILE_VIEWPORT_TESTING.md` for full guide

## Viewport Units

- Use `100svh` (not `100dvh`) for full-height mobile layouts so content fits when URL bar is visible
- `100svh` = small viewport (browser UI visible) = what users see on load
